nodes.bodyText:
I think I might be trying too hard. You're probably right that we should keep it simple, since I don't see us needing really fancy acceptors.
My original comment was thinking a little more generic, like:
    static <T> WaiterAcceptor<T> retryAttempsAcceptor(int maxAttempts) {
        return new WaiterAcceptor<T>() {
            private static AttributeKey<Integer> ATTEMPTS = AttributeKey.create("Attempts");

            @Override
            public WaiterState waiterState() {
                return WaiterState.FAILURE;
            }

            @Override
            public boolean matches(T response, WaiterExecutionContext context) {
                incrementAttempt(context);
                if (getAttempts(context) > maxAttempts) {
                    return true;
                }
                return false;
            }

            @Override
            public boolean matches(Throwable throwable, WaiterExecutionContext context) {
                incrementAttempt(context);
                if (getAttempts(context) > maxAttempts) {
                    return true;
                }
                return false;
            }

            private void incrementAttempt(WaiterExecutionContext context) {
                context.setAttribute(ATTEMPTS, getAttempts(context) + 1);
            }

            private int getAttempts(WaiterExecutionContext context) {
                Integer attempts = context.getAttribute(ATTEMPTS);
                return attempts == null ? 1 : attempts;
            }
        }
    }

